    • Method Detail

      • hashKey

        public int hashKey​(KType key)
        Description copied from class: ObjectCharHashMap
        Returns a hash code for the given key.

        The default implementation mixes the hash of the key with ObjectCharHashMap.keyMixer to differentiate hash order of keys between hash containers. Helps alleviate problems resulting from linear conflict resolution in open addressing.

        The output from this function should evenly distribute keys across the entire integer range.
